score.explanation: Your Wi-Fi network is in fair condition but facing competition from other networks.
score.trend_summary: Since last scan: download improved, upload stayed the same, ping worsened, networks increased.

latest_report.diagnosis: Your network is experiencing random dropouts, likely due to interference from neighboring networks. The number of competing networks is fairly high.

performance.interpretation: Your download speed is excellent, while the upload speed is somewhat below average. The ping latency is reasonable.

problems: High interference from surrounding networks on 2.4GHz band.
Conflicting channel usage among neighboring networks.
Suboptimal router placement affecting signal strength.
Limited upload bandwidth, especially during peak usage.
Random Wi-Fi disconnects affecting stable connectivity.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to 1 to reduce interference; currently on 6 and 11 (very congested).
Change the 5GHz channel to 149 for less congestion; currently using 36 which has multiple networks competing.
Consider repositioning the router closer to the center of the house for better coverage.
Enable QoS settings if available to prioritize gaming traffic.
Make sure that Smart Connect is enabled to optimize bandwidth usage.
